Introduction

   Please note that this readme is out of date since I have removed the
   uktvguide parser from the 0.1 release due to a possible legal problem.
   A new release using a different parser will be available soon.

   FreeGuide is an offline TV listings programme. It uses parser
   programmes to extract TV information from web pages and stores them
   for viewing without the need to connect to the Internet. The viewer
   allows the user to view television listings and create customised TV
   guides by selecting programmes and by building up a favourites list.
   For the moment, it only does UK listings, but it is designed to make
   it very easy to add other countries.

   FreeGuide is copyright ©2001 by Andy Balaam.  Please do send ideas,
   bugs and comments to me at [9]freeguide@artificialworlds.net. I
   welcome contributions from others. FreeGuide's home page is at
   [10]http://freeguide-tv.sourceforge.net. You can contact me at 1
   Winkfield Court, Boltro Road, Haywards Heath, United Kingdom, RH16
   1BH.

   FreeGuide uses (a small subset of) the XMLTV format developed by the
   very friendly people at XMLTV ([11]
   http://www.doc.ic.ac.uk/~epa98/work/apps/xmltv/ and
   [12]http://sourceforge.net/projects/xmltv ). In theory, FreeGuide
   should be able to work with the XMLTV grabbers as parsers, but this
   hasn't quite happened yet.  Again, any help would be greatly
   appreciated.

